Norwegian police say they are worried about the increase in men ordering child-like sex dolls from Hong Kong. JOHANNESBURG - Norwegian police say they are worried about the increase in men ordering child-like sex dolls from Hong Kong.The Associated Press is reporting that those who ve ordered the dolls, described as very lifelike, are men aged between 18 and 60 and include some convicted of sexual offences against children.Twenty-one dolls have been seized by customs since October and investigations continue.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)